IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/ucovenant47.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Covenant47</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/29/01 5:30:26 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why doesn't the goods take Odus?</span><hr size=1> The greatest advantage to being a good player is the fact that we hunt a lot of different places at different times.  I've leveled in Swamp of No Hope, FV, Iceclad, Kerra, etc.  &quot;Taking areas&quot; requires a commitment of high level goods to stop doing what we do best--porting around, wreaking havoc, taking the items we want, exping in remote locations, and moving on.  I don't want to babysit zones to fulfill some half-assed notion that our team is improved by &quot;controlling&quot; another zone, when in all likelyhood, nobody on my team will hunt there when I leave.<br>
<br>
In addition, I don't think the good team has the manpower to take another lowbie area.  It takes lowbies to take and hold lowbie areas.  This is why back when Blackburrow was really hotly contested, I'd clean it out for goods with a few friends, and it would be newt again the next day.  Low level goods weren't interested in hunting there due to the perceived risk.  After the initial raid is over, the high levels want a place to hunt (Stonebrunt, if it proves to be any good), and can't defend a zone like Warrens effectively.  Thus if a large number of low level goods dont move in, Warrens becomes evil again, and goods find themselves boxed into Stonebrunt.<br>
<br>
Zone control is determined by population and starting proximity.  (And in some cases, faction, as Ruin noticed).  PvP skill is great for raiding, but essentially meaningless in terms of holding zones long term.  If there were 3 times as many low level goods as there are, they'd be chafing to expand into new areas, and it would happen.  It would also happen if the zone in question were not halfway around the world from most goods.<br>
<br>
As for the relative merits of the zones in question, Warrens has great loot, mediocre experience, and horrible risk of death.  Kerra has good experience, poor loot, and can't be hunted really at all without harmony.  Stonebrunt, I don't know yet.  So the zones aren't exactly an overwhelming priority for anybody, though they certainly aren't bad.  Like I said though the reason we don't control Odus has more to do with the nature and size of the good team than any discussion of the relative merits of the Odus zones.<br>
-X. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/ubantonsz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BantonSZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/29/01 5:58:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why doesn't the goods take Odus?</span><hr size=1> Covenant has it exactly right. High levels may take over and dominate a zone, but it takes people who can xp there (and are thus willing to stay there for long periods of time) to hold a zone.<br>
<br>
If you have significanly more level appropriate people who want to be in that zone and those people have the things they need like banks and vendors near by, then you most likely will control the zone.<br>
<br>
BB would probably be controled by good right now except that EF/PF are better for singles and duos of low teens than QH/WK are. Both good and newt come to BB, but the newts stay because their local alteratives are less attractive. More newts xping there = newt controled. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uugliitchybottom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugli Itchybottom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/29/01 6:20:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why doesn't the goods take Odus?</span><hr size=1> Lootwise, Warrens is better than what good has access to.<br>
<br>
Trainwise, its simply ridiculous.  My Erud Necro headed to the swamp as soon as she hit 8 because its simply not possible to gain positive exp in Warrens with the high train frequency when there are more than about 2 groups in the zone.  The leveling to 8 was done mostly in the shithole known as Toxx forest for that same reason.  A train every 10 minutes is a gross understatement.  When I was there I'd say the odds of a getting hit by a train <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  during zone-in</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> were about 75%.  And that was just evils training evils before any newts or goods had tried to come over.<br>
<br>
Mistmoore has nothing on Warrens trainwise.  And MM has safe spots to camp in where the much less frequent trains don't path. <p><H3>Shamoo</H3><br>
